---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
import WaitlistForm from "../components/WaitlistForm.astro";
import "../styles/global.css";
---

<Base
  isHome
  title="ResearchReach — The Researcher Graph. Finally Searchable."
  description="Contact intelligence for academic researchers. Find pharma PIs, biotech consultants, and industry-adjacent scientists. Built on OpenAlex, ORCID, NIH Reporter, and PubMed. Join the waitlist."
>
  <main>
    <!-- NAV -->
    <header class="border-b border-navy-600 bg-navy/90 backdrop-blur-sm sticky top-0 z-40">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-4 flex items-center justify-between">
        <a href="/" class="font-display font-bold text-lg text-white no-underline">
          Research<span class="text-electric">Reach</span>
        </a>
        <nav class="hidden md:flex items-center gap-8">
          <a href="#how-it-works" class="text-slate text-sm hover:text-white no-underline transition-colors">How it works</a>
          <a href="#use-cases" class="text-slate text-sm hover:text-white no-underline transition-colors">Use cases</a>
          <a href="/developers" class="text-slate text-sm hover:text-white no-underline transition-colors">Developers</a>
          <a href="#waitlist" class="px-4 py-2 bg-electric text-white text-sm font-semibold rounded-lg no-underline hover:bg-electric-dim transition-colors">Join waitlist</a>
        </nav>
      </div>
    </header>

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="screen bg-navy flex items-center" id="top">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 py-24 md:py-32 w-full">
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-16 items-center">
          <div>
            <div class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-full px-4 py-2 mb-8">
              <span class="w-2 h-2 bg-mint rounded-full animate-pulse"></span>
              <span class="text-xs font-mono text-slate-light tracking-wider">EARLY ACCESS · 200+ TEAMS ON WAITLIST</span>
            </div>
            <h1 class="font-display text-[clamp(40px,6vw,72px)] font-black leading-[1.0] tracking-tight mb-6">
              The researcher<br />graph.<br />
              <span class="text-electric">Finally searchable.</span>
            </h1>
            <p class="text-slate-light text-lg md:text-xl leading-relaxed max-w-md mb-8">
              Find the right academic scientists — by field, funding, patents, and industry signals. Verified contacts, not LinkedIn guesses.
            </p>
            <div class="flex flex-wrap gap-3">
              <a href="#use-cases" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 text-slate-light text-sm rounded-lg no-underline hover:border-electric hover:text-white transition-colors">
                Pharma &amp; Biotech →
              </a>
              <a href="#use-cases" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 text-slate-light text-sm rounded-lg no-underline hover:border-electric hover:text-white transition-colors">
                Scientific Software →
              </a>
              <a href="/developers" class="inline-flex items-center gap-2 px-4 py-2 bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 text-slate-light text-sm rounded-lg no-underline hover:border-electric hover:text-white transition-colors">
                Developers API →
              </a>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <WaitlistForm
              id="waitlist-hero"
              heading="Get early access"
              subheading="Onboarding in waves. Work emails get priority."
            />
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROBLEM -->
    <section class="bg-navy-800 border-y border-navy-600 py-20 md:py-28" id="problem">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="max-w-3xl mx-auto text-center mb-16">
          <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(30px,4vw,52px)] font-bold leading-tight mb-6">
            Academic researchers are <span class="text-electric">invisible</span> to B2B tools.
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-light text-lg leading-relaxed">
            LinkedIn profiles are wrong or empty. ZoomInfo misses them entirely. Academic databases are 3 years stale. If your buyer is a PI, lab manager, or industry-adjacent scientist — you have no reliable way to reach them.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-6">
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🚫</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-2">LinkedIn is guesswork</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed">70% of researchers have no LinkedIn presence. Those who do rarely update institutional details or grant affiliations.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">📅</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-2">ZoomInfo misses academia</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed">Commercial databases index corporate HR systems. University researchers and NIH-funded PIs simply don't appear.</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🕳️</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-2">Databases are 3 years stale</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed">Faculty directories and publication databases update yearly at best. Lab moves, funding changes, and industry pivots go unrecorded.</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW IT WORKS -->
    <section class="bg-navy py-20 md:py-28" id="how-it-works">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="text-center mb-16">
          <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(30px,4vw,52px)] font-bold leading-tight mb-4">
            How it works
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-light text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">
            Three steps from search intent to verified contact export.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-electric flex items-center justify-center font-display font-bold text-white text-sm shrink-0">1</div>
              <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-navy-600 hidden md:block"></div>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white text-xl mb-3">Search by field, topic, or funding</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Query 250M+ papers. Filter by research area, active NIH/NSF grants, institutional affiliation, or publication recency. Find exactly the scientists you need.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 font-mono text-xs text-electric bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 rounded-lg p-3">
              <span class="text-slate"># Example query</span><br />
              field:"CRISPR gene editing"<br />
              funding:"NIH R01"<br />
              institution:"Stanford"
            </div>
          </div>
          <div class="relative">
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-electric flex items-center justify-center font-display font-bold text-white text-sm shrink-0">2</div>
              <div class="h-px flex-1 bg-navy-600 hidden md:block"></div>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white text-xl mb-3">Filter by industry signals</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Surface researchers with one foot in industry: patent holders, startup co-founders, SAB members, industry-funded PIs, and recent academia→industry transitions.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 text-mint px-2 py-1 rounded">patent_holder: true</span>
              <span class="text-xs font-mono bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 text-mint px-2 py-1 rounded">startup_affiliation: true</span>
              <span class="text-xs font-mono bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 text-mint px-2 py-1 rounded">industry_funding: true</span>
            </div>
          </div>
          <div>
            <div class="flex items-center gap-4 mb-6">
              <div class="w-10 h-10 rounded-full bg-electric flex items-center justify-center font-display font-bold text-white text-sm shrink-0">3</div>
            </div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white text-xl mb-3">Export verified contact + intent data</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed">
              Get institutional email addresses, ORCID profile, H-index, recent publications, grant amounts, and conference appearances — all in one export.
            </p>
            <div class="mt-4 flex flex-wrap gap-2">
              <span class="text-xs font-mono bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 text-slate-light px-2 py-1 rounded">CSV export</span>
              <span class="text-xs font-mono bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 text-slate-light px-2 py-1 rounded">CRM sync</span>
              <span class="text-xs font-mono bg-navy-800 border border-navy-600 text-slate-light px-2 py-1 rounded">REST API</span>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- USE CASES -->
    <section class="bg-navy-800 border-y border-navy-600 py-20 md:py-28" id="use-cases">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="text-center mb-16">
          <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(30px,4vw,52px)] font-bold leading-tight mb-4">
            Who uses ResearchReach
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-light text-lg max-w-xl mx-auto">
            Built for teams that sell to, recruit from, or invest in the scientific community.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-1 md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
          <a href="/use-cases#pharma" class="group bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 hover:border-electric rounded-xl p-8 no-underline transition-all">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🧬</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white text-xl mb-3 group-hover:text-electric transition-colors">Pharma &amp; Biotech Outreach</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Find PIs with active drug discovery grants. Identify researchers who've co-authored with industry teams. Build KOL lists with verified contacts, not stale rosters.
            </p>
            <span class="text-electric text-sm font-semibold">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/use-cases#software" class="group bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 hover:border-electric rounded-xl p-8 no-underline transition-all">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🖥️</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white text-xl mb-3 group-hover:text-electric transition-colors">Scientific Software Sales</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              For Benchling, Dotmatics, and ELN vendors. Reach lab managers and PIs who are actively publishing in your target verticals. Segment by lab size and funding level.
            </p>
            <span class="text-electric text-sm font-semibold">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/use-cases#recruiting" class="group bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 hover:border-electric rounded-xl p-8 no-underline transition-all">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">🔬</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white text-xl mb-3 group-hover:text-electric transition-colors">Deep Tech Recruiting</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Source PhD researchers with industry bridge signals. Filter by patent filings, startup co-founder credits, or recent transition from academia to industry.
            </p>
            <span class="text-electric text-sm font-semibold">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
          <a href="/use-cases#vc" class="group bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 hover:border-electric rounded-xl p-8 no-underline transition-all">
            <div class="text-3xl mb-4">💰</div>
            <h3 class="font-display font-bold text-white text-xl mb-3 group-hover:text-electric transition-colors">VC &amp; Deal Sourcing</h3>
            <p class="text-slate text-sm leading-relaxed mb-4">
              Track researchers filing patents in emerging fields before they spin out. Monitor NIH funding in your thesis areas. Surface the scientists most likely to found deep-tech companies.
            </p>
            <span class="text-electric text-sm font-semibold">Learn more →</span>
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DATA SOURCES -->
    <section class="bg-navy py-20 md:py-28" id="data-sources">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6">
        <div class="text-center mb-12">
          <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(28px,3.5vw,44px)] font-bold leading-tight mb-4">
            Built on open, authoritative data
          </h2>
          <p class="text-slate-light text-base max-w-xl mx-auto">
            We aggregate the world's best open research infrastructure — then layer proprietary industry signal detection on top.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="grid grid-cols-2 md:grid-cols-5 gap-4">
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
            <p class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-1">OpenAlex</p>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs">250M+ papers</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
            <p class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-1">ORCID</p>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs">20M+ researcher IDs</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
            <p class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-1">PubMed</p>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs">36M+ biomedical articles</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
            <p class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-1">NIH Reporter</p>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs">Active grant funding</p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-navy-700 border border-navy-600 rounded-xl p-6 text-center">
            <p class="font-display font-bold text-white mb-1">Semantic Scholar</p>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs">Citation intelligence</p>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div class="mt-8 text-center">
          <p class="text-slate text-sm">
            Plus: USPTO patent filings, Crossref DOI metadata, and proprietary industry transition signals.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- SOCIAL PROOF -->
    <section class="bg-navy-800 border-y border-navy-600 py-16 md:py-20" id="social-proof">
      <div class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
        <p class="font-display text-4xl md:text-5xl font-black text-white mb-4">200+</p>
        <p class="text-slate-light text-lg mb-12">teams already on the waitlist</p>
        <div class="flex flex-wrap justify-center gap-6 md:gap-12">
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-navy-600 flex items-center justify-center text-xl">🏥</div>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs font-mono">Pharma BD Lead</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-navy-600 flex items-center justify-center text-xl">💊</div>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs font-mono">Biotech Head of Sales</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-navy-600 flex items-center justify-center text-xl">🧪</div>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs font-mono">Lab Software AE</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-navy-600 flex items-center justify-center text-xl">🎯</div>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs font-mono">Deep Tech Recruiter</p>
          </div>
          <div class="flex flex-col items-center gap-2">
            <div class="w-12 h-12 rounded-full bg-navy-600 flex items-center justify-center text-xl">📈</div>
            <p class="text-slate text-xs font-mono">Life Sciences VC</p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FAQ -->
    <section class="bg-navy py-20 md:py-28" id="faq">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto px-6">
        <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(30px,4vw,52px)] font-bold leading-tight mb-12 text-center">
          Frequently asked questions
        </h2>
        <div class="divide-y divide-navy-600">
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-white cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
              How fresh is the data?
              <span class="text-electric text-xl font-bold transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 shrink-0">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-light text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              We sync with OpenAlex and Semantic Scholar weekly, PubMed daily, and NIH Reporter monthly. ORCID profiles are pulled on-demand. Most records are updated within 7 days of a new publication or funding award.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-white cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
              Is this GDPR-compliant?
              <span class="text-electric text-xl font-bold transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 shrink-0">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-light text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              Yes. We only index publicly-disclosed contact information (institutional emails listed in publications or on university pages) and public grant records. Researchers can request removal via our opt-out form. We follow GDPR legitimate interest grounds for B2B contact data.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-white cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
              How accurate are the email addresses?
              <span class="text-electric text-xl font-bold transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 shrink-0">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-light text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              We target &gt;85% deliverability on verified contacts. Institutional emails are cross-referenced against recent publications (last 24 months) to filter out stale records. We mark addresses as "high confidence", "likely valid", or "unverified" so you can prioritize.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-white cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
              What's the pricing model?
              <span class="text-electric text-xl font-bold transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 shrink-0">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-light text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              We're finalizing pricing. Early access users will lock in launch pricing. We plan a credit-based model (pay per export) with monthly subscription tiers for heavy users. API access will be separate. Join the waitlist to be first to know.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-white cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
              Is there an API for programmatic access?
              <span class="text-electric text-xl font-bold transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 shrink-0">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-light text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              Yes. We're building a REST API for scientific software vendors and data teams. See the <a href="/developers" class="text-electric-bright hover:underline">Developers page</a> for the schema and early access program. Python and Node.js SDK planned at launch.
            </p>
          </details>
          <details class="group py-6">
            <summary class="font-display text-lg font-semibold text-white cursor-pointer list-none flex items-center justify-between gap-4 [&::-webkit-details-marker]:hidden">
              How is this different from regular research databases like Scopus or Web of Science?
              <span class="text-electric text-xl font-bold transition-transform group-open:rotate-45 shrink-0">+</span>
            </summary>
            <p class="mt-4 text-slate-light text-base leading-relaxed max-w-2xl">
              Scopus and WoS are citation databases — built for academic research, not B2B prospecting. They don't surface contact information, industry signals, or grant data in a usable way. ResearchReach is a contact intelligence tool first: we're optimized for outreach and deal sourcing, not literature review.
            </p>
          </details>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- FINAL CTA -->
    <section class="bg-navy-800 border-t border-navy-600 py-20 md:py-28" id="waitlist">
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto px-6 text-center">
        <h2 class="font-display text-[clamp(28px,4vw,48px)] font-bold leading-tight mb-4">
          Ready to find the right scientists?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-slate-light text-lg mb-12">
          Join the waitlist. We're onboarding teams in waves — priority to use cases with the tightest fit.
        </p>
        <WaitlistForm
          id="waitlist"
          heading="Request early access"
          subheading="No spam. Unsubscribe anytime."
        />
      </div>
    </section>
  </main>
</Base>
